18 June - Finnish Pancake

- 3   tablespoon butter
- 2   eggs
- 2   cup milk
- 1   cup flour
- 1/4 teaspoon salt
- 1   tablespoon sugar

Preheat oven 375F put butter in pie plate and melt. In mixer beat eggs add milk beat together. In a medium bowl put flour mixture and beat 1 minute until smooth. Pour batter in pie plate - butter will come up to sides of batter. Bake 35-40 minutes until puffed and golden brown. Serve with syrup.